        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>The collection contains correspondence, manuscripts and subject files, most pertaining to Latin American cinema and his work for 
                <emph render="italic">Cineaste</emph>. PLEASE DIRECT FURTHER INQUIRIES TO: peter.filardo@nyu.edu</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Dan Georgakas is an anarchist,labor historian, scholar of Greek-American redicalism, and of motion pictures. Coauthor of 
                <emph render="italic">Detroit: I Do Mind Dying</emph> and coeditor of the 
                <emph render="italic">Encyclopedia of the American Left</emph> and he is a long time member of the 
                <emph render="italic">Cineaste</emph> editorial board, and has taught part time at New York University and Queens College.</p>
        </bioghist>
